'''Nara Shrine''' (ならじんじゃ) is a shrine located in Narachō, {{ill|lt=Tenri|Q502196|WD=Q502196|1=Tenri, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}.

=== Overview ===
Until around 1955 (Shōwa 30), it was called the shrine of {{ill|lt=Isaserihiko no Mikoto|Q65318|WD=Q65318|lt=Isaserihiko no Mikoto|1=Kibitsuhiko-no-mikoto}}. It was originally on Mt. Miyama (Higashi-Ōdera-yama), but is said to have been moved to the present location because it was far from the ujiko settlement.

In 1848 (Kōka 5), {{ill|lt=Ichikawa Danjūrō VIII|Q5986169|WD=Q5986169|lt=Ichikawa Danjūrō VIII|1=Ichikawa Danjūrō VIII}} dedicated a well curb.

